  <h3>Code Challenge</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>You will be adding a button group to the form in the HTML section of this Codepen, using the plugin that is documented <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.5/components/buttons/#checkbox-and-radio-buttons" target="_blank">here</a>. <strong>Read</strong> the documentation, then <strong>copy</strong> the example code for the three radio buttons there. <strong>Paste</strong> the example code to beneath where you see the comment that says <strong>"Your code additions will go below here."</strong></li>
    <li>Add the class <strong>col-4</strong> to the <strong>button-group</strong> div (the div element that has the button-group class on it).</li>
    <li>All radio buttons in a group must have the same <strong>name</strong>. Give all three radio buttons the name of <strong>"iceCreamFlavor"</strong>. </li>
    <li>All <strong>id</strong>s must be unique. Give them these three ids: <strong>"mintchocolate"</strong>, <strong>"vanilla"</strong>, and <strong>"strawberry"</strong>.</li>
    <li>Replace the text that follows each of the input elements (Active, Radio, Radio) with this text: <strong>Mint Chocolate</strong>, <strong>Vanilla</strong>, <strong>Strawberry</strong>.</li>
    <li>Add a <strong>value</strong> attribute for each radio input, with the text <strong>"mint chocolate"</strong>, <strong>"strawberry"</strong>, and <strong>"vanilla"</strong>.</li>
    <li>Using the <strong>Bootstrap button color classes</strong>, change the colors for each button so that they appear as in the screenshot below.</li>
    <li>Select each button and click the <strong>"Order"</strong> button, one at a time, to make sure that the text "You have placed an order for ..." appears correctly for each button.</li>
  </ol>
  
  <hr />
  <h3>Resources</h3>
